_[Understanding Class Members (The Java&amp;trade; Tutorials &amp;gt; Learning the Java Language &amp;gt; Classes and Objects)](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/classvars.html)_.

Essentially, when a _[field](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/variables.html)_, or _[method](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/methods.html)_, is defined as _static_, you will not need an _[instance](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/javaOO/objectcreation.html)_ to access them.\
Similar to the _[Math](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Math.html)_ class, which is composed of all _static_ _members_.

So, here is an example of an _instance_ _field_, and an _instance_ _method_.

```java
